    "body": "I'm struggling to work out what might have happened to lead you to this case... it might indeed be an interesting bug. Neither of the block hashes `0xa41eee2698f87b389edcd1a4f951ec5138f8f940b8d4079d93ffd6504924721a` or `0xae81b076b21c3b93c1b8c2c2c73f8c00102dc0d74af0f78405a0c74703be3250` seem to be blocks on Altona. Is it possible that you had a datadir lying around from running a Witti node previously? Did you re-use the same `lighthouse-docker` directory (which would have contained `.lighthouse/beacon`, possibly with Witti state)?\r\n\r\nYou mention that this was the second time you ran the beacon node, when did you first run it?",
